Paper: hep-th/9805113

Date: 1998-05-18

Title: Sigma-model Solutions and Intersecting p-Branes Related to Lie Algebras

Authors: M. A. Grebeniuk and V. D. Ivashchuk

Comments: 13 pages, LaTeX, submitted to Phys. Lett. B

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B442 (1998) 125-135

A family of Majumdar-Papapetrou type solutions in sigma-model of p-braneorigin is obtained for all direct sums of finite-dimensional simple Liealgebras. Several examples of p-brane dyonic configurations in D=10 (IIA) andD=11 supergravities corresponding to the Lie algebra sl(3,C) are considered.